<span class="name"><a name="92182"></a></span><span class="postdetails">#1:&nbsp;<font color=black><b>Most fun in a while</b> Author:&nbsp;<b>Sinya</b>,&nbsp;</font></span><span class="postdetails"><font color=black></font></span>
<a href="viewtopic.php?p=92182#92182"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails"><font color=black>Posted: Thu Jan 06, 2005 11:20 pm</font><span class="gen"><br>
</td></tr>
<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">It has been a while since I have been in a group set up where there were mobs in camp, mez was desperately needed, healers were low mana, but the other night....
<br />

<br />
Cleric, 2 beastlords, shaman, me, and an ebay warrior had WoS to ourselves.  One of the beastlords was pulling and the group was generally tearing things up.  High dps, fast pulls no problems (other then educating the warrior on how to break mez without getting me beat on).
<br />

<br />
The puller grabs a Bazu Smasher named and dies on inc after picking up the Chimera Seether named.  No worries, I mez the Bazu and the Chimera gets beaten down to about 15%.  The next two minutes were just about the wildest ride I have had in a long time.
<br />

<br />
The tank dies.  With the wonderful amount of agro from tash, the new cripple and a couple of nukes I am the Chimera's best friend.  The next two minutes were a desperate fight to chain rune, refresh mez on the Bazu and another add that showed up.  The remaining beastlord was desperately trying to take agro or at least do enough damage to finish the Chimera.  The entire time the Chimera is pounding on me, while the shaman and cleric are spamming heals to keep me up.
<br />

<br />
When it was all done, the Chimera died.  The healers were OOM and we fled with a hard won rune.  The desperate race to channel the mez to ensure the Bazu didn't wipe the rest of the group was awesome and the best part was I lived!</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
<br />
